text/plain: "Salesforce Business Systems Analyst - job post KDInfotech 5 reviews San Francisco, CA • Remote $145,000 - $175,000 a year -  Full-time Apply now Apply now save-icon Job details Salary $145,000 - $175,000 a year Job Type Full-time A Day in the Life of our Salesforce Business Systems Analyst (BSA) Our Salesforce BSA works closely with business users to gather business requirements, develop user stories, process changes and improve work flows. By doing so they solve business problems and lead the agile process for Salesforce. They deliver high quality solutions which meet business needs and support ongoing integrations of new features and capabilities. The Salesforce BSA also tracks deliverables daily to ensure deadlines are met, and communicate Salesforce deliverables to the team leads and stakeholders. They are our SME’s (Subject Matter Experts) of the Salesforce platform and provide ongoing support. They act as a trusted business partner to Compliance, Customer Support, Legal, and Sales leaders. Salesforce BSA owns the inception, analysis, design,and user-acceptance testing phase of the Agile development process for SFDC. Additionally, they work closely with compliance teams to meet or exceed regulatory requirements. Who Should Apply Your previous experience should showcase your ability to perform routine changes and upgrades to the Salesforce platform and be a Salesforce SME. We encourage you to apply if you have a background in gathering requirements, speaking to various stakeholders to gather improvement and integration changes to salesforce. The ideal candidate will have a deep understanding of healthcare regulatory frameworks to provide guidance to business partners. Responsibilities Provide ongoing support for Salesforce evolution, drive platform producibility Ensuring the roadmap is aligned with the stakeholders expectations Understand cross functional impacts of business requirements to configure, process, workflow, reporting and incorporate all into user support interactions Drive the requirements gathering process with heavy emphasis on compliance with HIPAA, SOX, GDPR, ISO 27000, CCPA, and other privacy frameworks. Collaborate with leadership across the enterprise to ensure feature pipeline aligns with functional and company goals Document analysis and design within compliance requirements Document and proctor user-acceptance tests Support regulatory audits of the IT Salesforce System Lead the team’s efforts to be compliance and audit ready Support auditors during the audit process with evidence collection Qualifications and Skills 4+ years of experience in technical support role with Salesforce 3+ years of experience in business analytics Salesforce Certified Administrator Certification preferred General knowledge of the JIRA Confluence Suite PMP or MBA in project management or equivalent job experience Bachelor's Degree or equivalent work experience Job Type: Full-time Pay: $145,000.00 - $175,000.00 per year Benefits: 401(k) 401(k) matching Dental insurance Employee assistance program Health insurance Health savings account Life insurance Paid time off Vision insurance Experience level: 4 years Schedule: 8 hour shift Monday to Friday Work Location: Remote Health insurance If you require alternative methods of application or screening, you must approach the employer directly to request this as Indeed is not responsible for the employer's application process."

def clean_text(txt):   
    wcount=len(txt)
    corpus=[]
    #remove punctuation
    text=re.sub('[^a-zA-Z]',' ',txt)

    #lowercase
    text=text.lower()

    #remove tags
    text=re.sub("</?.*?>"," <> ",text)

    #remove special characters and digits
    text=re.sub("(\\d|\\W)+"," ",text)

    # string to list
    text=text.split()

    #stemming
    ps=PorterStemmer()

    #lemmatisation
    lem=WordNetLemmatizer()
    text=[lem.lemmatize(word) for word in text if not word in stop_words]
    text=" ".join(text)

    corpus.append(text)
    
    return corpus

def show_wordcloud(txt):
    wordcloud = WordCloud(
                              background_color='white',
                              stopwords=stop_words,
                              max_words=100,
                              max_font_size=50, 
                              random_state=42
                             ).generate(str(clean_text(txt)))
    plt.rcParams["figure.figsize"] = (10,5)
    fig = plt.figure(1)
    plt.imshow(wordcloud)
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.show()
